x4freetext: A diffusion cloud chamber filled with helium at
edge parallel to  the  direction  of  the  gamma-ray
The usual interpretation of the photoneutron  spectra
in terms of evaporation with a small contribution of
direct  reaction  is  not  in  agreement  with   the
experimental results for neutron energies lower than
1.5 MeV.  Qualitative discussion of other models  is
given  to  explain  the  experimental  indication of
photoneutron polarization found for Mn-55 and Co-59.
Detailed  description  of  the  experiment is in the
paper by A.De Marco,  R.Garfagnini, G.Piragino, Atti
